  "text": "proportional to) the conductance (in \u03a9 \u22121 ) of photoresistors will also fail in GaN-based devices because their conductive volume is not equal to the whole volume of the GaN material. There are depleted regions under their surfaces because nGaN tends to hold electrons in surface states (SEs). The SBB is derived from the double layer (DL) formed by the negative charges trapped in occupied SEs and the positive charges of a depleted region of thickness . The collapse of GaN FETs is a dramatic effect of this behaviour of n-GaN surfaces that is capable of forming a negative floating gate on the surface of these devices [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
